{
  "stem": "18258.2",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But during the summer, in Vienna Book Garten, they had regular concerts, and I went there many times, again restricted by availability of cold cash.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Because for those things, you had to pay.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I was bar mitzvah, very peculiar.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I became 13 and Grandmother, who was the Orthodox lady, and-- wanted me to become bar mitzvah'd.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Now, normally, you went to Hebrew school a couple of years before.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "In my case, my dad took me to the local rabbi-- we knew where he lived.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "He lived in a-- same street as we were.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And Dad took me there one afternoon and said, I would like my son to become bar mitzvah.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "His birthday is then and then.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And the rabbi checked his calendar and said, well, the 6th of September, we have one opening.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "The [NON-ENGLISH] is already given away for that day, but he can come up there and join the [NON-ENGLISH] boy and say the [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "More, he can do-- can't do anyway.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "So he let me recite the [NON-ENGLISH], which I had memorized at home.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "The rabbi said, OK.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "At that-- on that day, it was a Saturday, of course, you come to the synagogue, and you'll join the [NON-ENGLISH] boy at the [? bima, ?] and you will say the [NON-ENGLISH], and that will be your bar mitzvah.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "In the afternoon, I had a few family members at home for coffee and cake.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And that was the reception.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And in late afternoon, then we had my classmates.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "That was-- we were all in the-- about the same age.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And every other Saturday or some, there was another party for classmates.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "We didn't care for the religious aspect of it.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "For us, it was the party.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "We exchanged little gifts.",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
